{{Infobox journal | title = Communication Research Reports | image = 2018_CCR_cover.jpg | former_name = <!-- or |former_names= --> | abbreviation = Commun. Res. Rep. | discipline = [[Communication studies]] | editor = Nicholas D. Bowman | publisher = [[Routledge]] | history = 1984-present | frequency = Quarterly | openaccess = [[Hybrid open access journal|Hybrid]] | license = | impact = | impact-year = | ISSN = 0882-4096 | eISSN = 1746-4099 | CODEN = | JSTOR = | LCCN = sn85001024 | OCLC = 321019859 | website = https://www.tandfonline.com/action/journalInformation?show=aimsScope&journalCode=rcrr20 | link1 = https://www.tandfonline.com/toc/rcrr20/current?nav=tocList | link1-name = Online access | link2 = https://www.tandfonline.com/loi/rcrr20 | link2-name = Online archive }} '''''Communication Research Reports''''' is a quarterly [[peer-reviewed]] academic journal covering [[communication studies]]. It was established in 1984 and is published by [[Routledge]].
The journal specializes in the publication of reports-style manuscripts using social scientific methods (such as quantitative data analysis). The most common type of manuscripts published are research reports, which often feature "scales, causal models, novel correlations, and immediate observations — constitute the 'nuts and bolts' of human communication..."<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Bowman |first1=Nicholas |title=Research Reports as the "Nuts and Bolts" of Communication Research |journal=Communication Research Reports |date=13 April 2016 |volume=33 |issue=2 |page=87 |doi=10.1080/08824096.2016.1174536}}</ref>
In 2016, the journal was rated as the third-most central to the field of [[human communication]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Griffin |first1=Darrin J |last2=Bolkan |first2=San |last3=Holmgrem |first3=Jennifer |last4=Tutzauer |first4=Frank |title=Central journals and authors in communication using a publication network |journal=[[Scientometrics (journal)|Scientometrics]] |date=January 2016 |volume=106 |issue=1 |pages=91–104 |doi=10.1007/s11192-015-1774-4}}</ref>
==Abstracting and indexing== The journal is abstracted and indexed in [[EBSCO Information Services|EBSCO databases]], [[PsycINFO]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.apa.org/pubs/databases/psycinfo/coverage.aspx |publisher=[[American Psychological Association]] |title=PsycINFO Journal Coverage |accessdate=2018-03-25}}</ref> and [[Scopus]].<ref name=Scopus>{{cite web |url=https://www.scopus.com/sourceid/5700155425 |title=Source details: Communication Research Reports |publisher=[[Elsevier]] |work=Scopus preview |accessdate=2018-03-25}}</ref>
